<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-18194] PaxosPrepare may add instances to the Electorate that are not in gossip</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18194</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.cassandra.service.paxos.PaxosPrepare.RequestHandler#execute is given a list of electorate from the peer and attempts to compute its own, then replies back with this set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the peer side, we then have the set we sent and the set from the other instance... we then fetch the EndpointState from Gossiper and store into a Map, a map we later attempt to inject into Gossip.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is possible that Gossiper does not know about the instance yet, so returns a null; causing a NullPointerException in downstream code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
